The following tweets are some important information regarding prevention of #dengue
1. Prevention = avoiding mosquito bites. #dengue
2. It is important to participate in reducing mosquitoes by eliminating the places where the mosquito lays her eggs. #dengue
3. Indoors: artificial containers that hold water, look for standing water indoors such as in vases (clean at least once a week) #dengue
4. Outdoors: clean water containers like pet and animal watering containers, flower planter dishes or cover water storage barrels. #dengue
5. The adult mosquitoes like to bite inside as well as around homes, during the day and at night when the lights are on. #dengue
6. So, to protect yourself, don‚Äôt forget to use repellent on your skin while indoors or out. #dengue
7. wear long sleeves and pants for additional protection, if possible. #dengue #protectyourself
8. make sure window and door screens are secure and without holes. #dengue #protectyourself
9. use air-conditioning and sleep under a mosquito bed net, if available. #dengue #protectyourself
